 ('12', '28', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vegan Thai Larb Lettuce Cups\",\"slug\":\"vegan-thai-larb-lettuce-cups\",\"postDate\":1500057825,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"13\":\"\",\"20\":[\"14\"],\"3\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"paragraph\":\"<p>I\'ll be the first to admit that I\'ve always been rather skeptical and intimidated by the idea of veganism. To me, it\'s always sounded like a buzz word that implies a rigid restriction and deprivation around food which, for someone who loves food as much as I do, is a huge turn off. In our society, there\'s so much baggage tied to food and eating, and morality is inextricably linked to healthy eating. If you\'re a vegan, you\'re a good, righteous person who stands up for helpless animals and treats your body as a temple. If you\'re a meat eater, you\'re an indulgent carnivore that\'s ruled by your primal cravings.<\\/p><p>These stereotypes have always made me feel like I\'ve had to pick a side and stay within my lane. I don\'t eat vegan because I\'m not \\\"that type of person\\\". But lately, now that I\'ve embarked on my own journey towards getting healthy and becoming a health coach, my ideas have began to shift. I\'m realizing that my relationship to food as not as black and white as I\'ve always made it out to be and my food choices should be ruled by my body instead of my mind. If my body wants a steak then I want to give it the fattest, juciest steak I can get my hands on. If my body is craving vegetables, I want to feed it a ripe, colorful, diverse array of veggies. My body knows what it needs and the more I tap in and listen to that, the healthier and more fulfilled I will be.<\\/p><p>That said, at one point if someone told me that I would voluntarily make one of my favorite recipes, Thai Larb lettuce cups, &nbsp;into a vegan recipe I would have balked and probably even gagged at the idea. But here I am, replacing ground beef with vegan tempeh in this fresh, delicious recipe and loving every bite. I don\'t even recognize myself anymore.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":[\"11\"],\"singleImage\":\"\",\"imageRow\":\"\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":\"\",\"singleImage\":\"\",\"imageRow\":[\"7\",\"8\"]}}},\"14\":\"\",\"12\":\"Perfect for a quick and tasty lunch!\",\"2\":\"\"}}', '2017-07-14 18:43:45', '2017-07-14 18:43:45', '31be50c4-0c98-4d2e-8ec7-9090b4c40db9'),
 ('13', '28', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vegan Thai Larb Lettuce Cups\",\"slug\":\"vegan-thai-larb-lettuce-cups\",\"postDate\":1500057780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"13\":\"\",\"20\":[\"14\"],\"3\":{\"29\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"paragraph\":\"<p>I\'ll be the first to admit that I\'ve always been rather skeptical and intimidated by the idea of veganism. To me, it\'s always sounded like a buzz word that implies a rigid restriction and deprivation around food which, for someone who loves food as much as I do, is a huge turn off. In our society, there\'s so much baggage tied to food and eating, and morality is inextricably linked to healthy eating. If you\'re a vegan, you\'re a good, righteous person who stands up for helpless animals and treats your body as a temple. If you\'re a meat eater, you\'re an indulgent carnivore that\'s ruled by your primal cravings.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>These stereotypes have always made me feel like I\'ve had to pick a side and stay within my lane. I don\'t eat vegan because I\'m not \\\"that type of person\\\". But lately, now that I\'ve embarked on my own journey towards getting healthy and becoming a health coach, my ideas have began to shift. I\'m realizing that my relationship to food as not as black and white as I\'ve always made it out to be and my food choices should be ruled by my body instead of my mind. If my body wants a steak then I want to give it the fattest, juciest steak I can get my hands on. If my body is craving vegetables, I want to feed it a ripe, colorful, diverse array of veggies. My body knows what it needs and the more I tap in and listen to that, the healthier and more fulfilled I will be.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>That said, at one point if someone told me that I would voluntarily make one of my favorite recipes, Thai Larb lettuce cups, &nbsp;into a vegan recipe I would have balked and probably even gagged at the idea. But here I am, replacing ground beef with vegan tempeh in this fresh, delicious recipe and loving every bite. I don\'t even recognize myself anymore.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"30\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":[\"11\"],\"singleImage\":\"\",\"imageRow\":\"\"}},\"31\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":\"\",\"singleImage\":\"\",\"imageRow\":[\"7\",\"8\"]}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"recipe\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"recipeImage\":[\"6\"],\"ingredients\":\"<ul><li>1 block of tempeh<\\/li><li>Fresh Herbs- Parsley, cilantro, mint, dill, basil<\\/li><li>1 head of lettuce broken up as cups<\\/li><li>1 persian cucumber, sliced<\\/li><li>1\\/2 onion<\\/li><li>1 Jalapeno<\\/li><li>5 garlic bulbs<\\/li><li>a big chunk of ginger<\\/li><li>1 lime<\\/li><li>1 lemon<\\/li><li>Soy Sauce<\\/li><li>Honey<\\/li><li>1 tbsp crushed peanuts<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"recipeSummary\":\"<p>Start by steaming the tempeh in a sauce pan by adding a shallow layer of salt water. Let the tempeh &nbsp;steam for at least 10 minutes until it is soft and can be easily crumbled.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>Finely slice the onion, ginger, garlic and jalapeno and add them together to create a thick paste. Add coconut oil to a hot cast iron pan and add salt, pepper and sesame seeds. Let the sesame seeds toast until they are brown and fragrant. Add the veggie mixture and cook until they are golden brown, then throw in the crumbled tempeh. Mix all ingredients together, adding a dash of soy sauce, honey and the juice of a lime. Sprinkle fresh cut herbs into the mixture and some pink peppercorns for kick.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>While the tempeh is cooking, assemble the fresh herbs, lettuce cups, tomatoes and crushed peanuts. Serve together, allowing each person to assemble their own lettuce cups as desired.<\\/p>\"},\"collapsed\":\"1\"},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":\"\",\"singleImage\":[\"10\"],\"imageRow\":\"\"},\"collapsed\":\"\"},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":\"\",\"singleImage\":[\"9\"],\"imageRow\":\"\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fullBleedImage\":\"\",\"singleImage\":\"\",\"imageRow\":[\"12\",\"13\",\"15\"]}}},\"14\":[\"18\"],\"12\":\"Perfect for a quick and tasty lunch!\",\"2\":[\"32\",\"33\",\"34\"]}}', '2017-07-14 19:04:57', '2017-07-14 19:04:57', '3198a37b-216a-40fa-8a87-71ebf5a32e06'),
